Includes teaching of neurological examination of the patients, systematic review of diagnosis and treatment of  the diseases  of the brain and spinal cord, peripheral nerves and muscles.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to teach neurological examination and diagnostic possibilities of the patients with disorders of the brain, spinal cord, peripheral nerves and muscles. To teach differential diagnosis and primary management options of critically ill patient.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student will: 1. Know the principles of communicating with the patients having neurological or neurosurgical disorders 2. Be able to suspect and recognize the possibility of neurological disease, based on patient's complaints 3. Know most relevant aspects of neurological topical diagnosis 4. Be able to perform neurological clinical examination and logically suggest possible diagnosis 5. Knows most concerned laboratory, instrumental and radiological methods used in neurology and neurosurgery 6. Knows prevalence, diagnostic criteria, principles of treatment (medical and rehabilitation) of major neurological and neurosurgical diseases
